## Project Identity
name: "Rust Project"
description: "Rust application"
version: "0.1.0"

## Tech Stack
- Language: Rust (stable)
- Build: Cargo
- Testing: cargo test

## Coding Style
- Follow Rust naming conventions
- Use Result<T, E> for error handling
- Prefer iterators over manual loops
- Use derive macros where applicable
- Document public APIs using docstrings

## Constraints
- No unsafe code without thorough documentation
- Handle all Result and Option types explicitly
- Use clippy and rustfmt
